abstract: Asian stock markets jumped Wednesday, powered by better-than-expected earnings from chipmaking giant Intel and Singapore’s forecast that its economy will grow a blistering 15 percent this year.
snippet: Asian stock markets jumped Wednesday, powered by better-than-expected earnings from chipmaking giant Intel and Singapore’s forecast that its economy will grow a blistering 15 percent this year.
lead_paragraph: Asian stock markets jumped Wednesday, powered by better-than-expected earnings from the chip making giant, Intel, and Singapore’s forecast that its economy will grow a blistering 15 percent this year, The Associated Press reported.

headline.main: Asian Stocks Up, Powered by Intel and Singapore
